            "title"=> "CARDBOARD CORRUGATED OR RIGID BOXES  WHICH IS BEST FOR SHOE PACKAGING?",
            "slug"=> "cardboard-corrugated-or-rigid-boxes-which-is-best-for-shoe-packaging",
            "body"=> "<p>There&rsquo;s something indescribable about buying a brand new pair of shoes. When you try it on for the first, when it fits well and the first fresh walk   it all gives a unique sense of joy. We all love to have a variety of pairs from which we can select the one we find most fit for ourselves. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As consumers, we mostly like the shoes on the basis of various sidelining factors such as, price, quality, and how well it suits us. All of these are fair perspectives to consider before making a favourable purchase.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, there is also another deciding factor <a href=\"https=>//bestcustomboxes.co.uk/product/shoe-boxes/\">Shoe Boxes</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The way you have presented your shoes in the market, or online in the case of e-commerce, can make a huge difference. Now there should be many factors that altogether make your  Shoe Packaging  worth the hype and attraction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first aspect is obviously the material you will be using in making your  <a href=\"https=>//bestcustomboxes.co.uk/\">custom packaging</a> . The material you choose for your boxes will eventually enable you to add features and add-ons in your packaging. Meanwhile, the most commonly used materials for shoe packaging are corrugated, cardboard, rigid and kraft.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, let&rsquo;s have a look at a comparison between cardboard corrugated and rigid boxes&rsquo; material.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2> Cardboard Corrugated Shoe Boxes </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>These boxes are made with corrugated board which consist of multiple fluted sheets glued together. They are more sturdy and durable than plain cardboard sheets. This quality makes these boxes more preferable for semi-heavy products packaging like shoes. In general, they are used for shipping purposes. So, we can often find mailer boxes made with corrugated material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, to make it innovatively unique among others, you can customize your  Shoe Packaging  in different shapes and designs. Furthermore, you can add features like lamination, foiling, surface coating, plain or digital printing to die-cut shapes to enhance product appeal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These boxes are considered most fit for retail purposes. But they can also be used for packaging of the shoes that require a little more protection such as, female wearables and vulnerable shoe sets.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2> Benefits of Cardboard Corrugated Boxes </h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li> Sustainable => Once used, they can be recycled completely that makes them decent choice if you are looking for sustainable packaging solution.</li>\r\n  <li> Durability => These are highly durable boxes. Moreover, with the moisture content ranging from 6.5%   9.5%, they can certainly keep your shoes protected from moist and humidity of the environment.</li>\r\n  <li> Light   weight => These boxes are sturdy enough to keep your goods protected. But these boxes are still light weight. Thereby, more convenient for handling.</li>\r\n  <li> Affordable => They are also relatively expensive as compared to other  <a href=\"https=>//bestcustomboxes.com/\">packaging boxes</a> .</li>\r\n  <li> Branding   and   Customization => You can easily customize and print these boxes to make your packaging exclusive and different. Moreover, you can also have them prepared in custom shapes, sizes and designs with your logo and brand name added to help you create an authentic brand image.</li>\r\n  <li> Add   ons => It is very easy to write on these custom boxes even after the production, so you can direct write upon them as well. You can also add custom labels, stickers and tags in the packaging.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course, there are also a few drawbacks to consider.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2> Drawbacks of Cardboard Corrugated Boxes </h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li> Not   Long   Lasting => Although the material is recyclable. But you can not use the box for other purposes after specific time.</li>\r\n  <li> Less Durable Than Rigid Boxes => Although they are durable enough to protect your shoes from external damages, but they can&rsquo;t guarantee protection in case of rare misfortunate situations such as, extreme pressure or rain etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2> Rigid Shoe Boxes </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Rigid Shoe Boxes are made with strong paperboard material. But they can also cost you a little more than casual boxes. Thus, they are majorly used by renowned brands and for packing high-end products. It also has a significantly higher carbon footprint than  <a href=\"https=>//bestcustomboxes.co.uk/product/corrugated-boxes/\">corrugated packaging</a> .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It offers an excellent mix of product protection and perceived luxury. You can use it for packaging of high end and expensive shoes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2> Benefits of Rigid Shoe Boxes </h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li> Highly Durable=>  Rigid Boxes are the most sound packaging boxes available in the market, besides metal boxes.</li>\r\n  <li> Customizable=>  You can have your boxes made in different shapes, designs and features to create the most ideal packaging box for your shoe brand. Moreover, you can also have different range of  Shoe Boxes  for your every shoe type range.</li>\r\n  <li> Luxurious Appeal=>  You can also add printed and embellished sheets of paper with add ons and features. So this packaging instantly levels up your packaging, giving your products a royal and high end appeal instantly.</li>\r\n  <li> Branding=>  You can also add your brand name and logo with certain illustration and certain colour code to give your packaging a peculiar touch. This will help you in creating a worthy brand image in the market.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2> Drawbacks of Rigid Shoe Boxes </h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li> High Cost=>  This type of boxes comes quite expensive relatively to other material packaging.</li>\r\n  <li> Expensive Shipping=>  As they weigh more so they may charge you extra shipping charges as well.</li>\r\n  <li> Non-recyclable => They can not be recycled.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3> Packaging Design Options in Both Materials </h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Meanwhile, you can choose any of the materials for your shoes. But it would require you to do a deep analysis of your product requirements, packaging demands, budget and your expectations for sales outcomes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, despite the material you choose, you can have it created in custom shapes and sizes such as,  <a href=\"https=>//bestcustomboxes.co.uk/product/sleeve-boxes/\">sleeve boxes</a> , collapsible boxes, <a href=\"https=>//bestcustomboxes.co.uk/product/two-piece-boxes/\"> two piece boxes</a>  with window lid, one-piece boxes, and  <a href=\"https=>//bestcustomboxes.co.uk/product/mailer-boxes/\">mailer boxes</a> .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Meanwhile, both boxes have their own benefits and drawbacks. It would be most beneficial for you to make a choice as per your marketing requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>So, which one you&rsquo;re getting for yourself?</em></p>",
