            "body"=> "<p>Cigarettes are one of the few things in the world that are clearly advertised with the harmful side effects it has on its consumers, yet public never ceases to buy it. Therefore, we can often find Printed Cigarette Packaging with gruesome pictures and illustrations conveying the message clearly to its buyers that it causes cancer, respiratory disorders and other illnesses. However, still it is one of the most consumed product in the world. Despite all the legal interventions and being banned in many regions, people can&rsquo;t seem to get enough of it, and thus, tobacco still remains the most consumed among people of different age groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, it was not always the case.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> <a href=\"https=>//bestcustomboxes.co.uk/product/cigarette-boxes/\">Cigarette Packaging</a> has not always been this controversial or came with such warning labels, instead with rather opposite, quite inviting pictures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When it was first introduced in early 19th&nbsp;century, it was referred as harmless and even&nbsp;<em>healthy</em>&nbsp;past time activity. It was advertised as a choice of healthy citizens. It becomes considerably popular in the America after renowned manufacturer intrigued the public to buy war bonds along with promoting its own product. During the time of Second World War, it was considered as the preference and favorite past time of American soldiers in all over the United States. Meanwhile, by hitting the right spot and evoking the patriotic emotions in majority of the population, they were clearly successful with their emotional marketing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was certainly enjoyed by the soldiers at that time, even though they were required to be in their prime health condition in order to fight the challenges. But the technology and studies were not so progressive about it at that time. So they consumed and renowned brands took advantage of the opportunity by marketing the perspective and encouraging thousan